post_text: With the recent decision by the USDA we will be providing meals (breakfast and lunch) at no charge for all students beginning today. We will still be charging for seconds (extra entree) or a second milk. The USDA announcement runs through December 31st of this year or until funding runs out. We are still receiving guidance on this and will continue to update you as more information comes in.

post_text:
*Currently only 52% of Max residents have completed the census!
*You have until October 31, 2020 to complete your #2020Census. Go to my2020census.gov and be counted TODAY!
If you spend at least 51% of your time in North Dakota, you need to be counted here. By being counted, you help direct federal funding to necessary resources like the Disabled Vets Outreach Program, education, and health care services.
We live with the impact from this count for the next ten years!

HELP NEEDED in the Community Garden!
Prepping & Planting:
Thursday, May 14th from 4-7pm
Meet in the community garden area which is west of the baseball field.

Call or text Amanda Huettl (701-240-2034) if you are able to help or have questions so we can plan for those volunteering!

Please feel free to bring anything that may be helpful.

*Due to current school restrictions, the FFA members are not able to plant the community garden. If you are able, please volunteer your time to help with a garden that gives so much to our community.

*No students or children under the age of 18 can participate at this time.

*If we are unable to plant due to weather, we will reschedule and post it.

post_text: Softball is in our spotlight for today! This program was started last year and we were looking forward to another exciting year with the girls. Thank you to Nygard Construction, Scheresky Ag, and the Max Farmers Elevator for donating materials and equipment.

Max FFA Scholarship Winners-Local and National Scholarship Winners

The Max FFA and Max FFA Alumni are proud and excited to announce the following winners of our scholarships for 2020! Congratulations to all of our winners!

Camden Johnson: Max FFA Alumni Scholarship for $300 & Max FFA Scholarship for $300. Camden will be attending Trinity Bible College in the fall and he plans to return to the Douglas area to farm following graduation from college.

Aubrey Black: Max FFA Alumni Scholarship for $500. Aubrey plans to attend Minot State University in the fall and earn a degree in social work.

Christina Bingham: College Max FFA Alumni Scholarship for $300. Christina is majoring in nursing at the University of Mary. Christina was also awarded a scholarship from the National FFA Organization. She received a $1000 scholarship sponsored by Ford Trucks/Built Ford Tough-FFA Scholarship National Program.

Due to the following statement, all remaining fine arts and spring sports are suspended indefinitely.

March 13, 2020 2:45 pm

FARGO ‚Äì On Friday, March 13, due to the Emergency Declaration issued by President Trump the NDHSAA will suspend play at the 2020 NDHSAA Class A Basketball State Tournament and all remaining 2020 NDHSAA Winter Postseason State Tournaments including the 2020 NDHSAA Class B Boys Basketball State Tournament.

In addition to the remaining 2020 NDHSAA Winter Postseason Basketball State Tournaments being suspended, all remaining fine arts and spring sports seasons have been suspended indefinitely, which includes practices and game contests. Further information will be released as it becomes available.
